cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically syntactic parsing. The use of a structured variational autoencoder also suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel generative model and uses dynamic programming, which are both relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of stochastically perturbed edge scores and differentiable relaxation suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
